{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἀπονίζω</b>, <br /> later <b>ἀπονευρ-νίπτω</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" D.S 4.59, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Phocion” 18, and once as variant in 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>], see below:— <b>wash off,</b> ἀπονίψαντες.. βρότον ἐξ ὠτειλῶν[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 24.18), compare 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 7.425 (tmesis)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>middle</i>, <b>wash off from oneself,</b> ἱδρῶ πολλὸν ἀπονίζοντο θαλάσσῃ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 10.572. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>wash clean,</b> especially of the hands and feet, τὴν ἀπονίζουσα φρασάμην I perceived it (the scar) <b>as</b> I <b>was washing his feet,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 23.75; ὅταν ἡ θυγάτηρ μ᾽ ἀπονίζῃ καὶ τὼ πόδ᾽ ἀλείφῃ 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 608, compare 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus “Γεωργός” 60; ἓ μὲν ἔφη ἀ. τὸν παῖδα 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Symposium” 175a:\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] —<i>middle</i>, χρῶτ᾽ ἀπονίπτεσθαι <b>wash one's</b> body, variant in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 18.179, compare 172; χεῖράς τε πόδας τε [prev. work] 22.478: _absolutely_, οἷον εἴ τις εἰς πηλὸν ἐμβὰς πηλῷ -νίζοιτο 1st c.AD(?): Heraclitus 5\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <b>wash one's hands</b> (especially after meals,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"compare 3rd-2nd c.BC: Aristophanes Byzantinus Philosophus cited in 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 9.408f), 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “γυναικεῖα” 1.89; ἐγὼ μὲν ἀποτρέχων ἀπονίψομαι 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Aves” 1163; ἀπονίψασθαι δοτέον \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>water to wash with,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Alexander Rhetor 250, compare 4th c.BC: Antiphanes Comicus 136\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; so in <i>perfect</i> <i>passive</i>, ἀπονενίμμεθ᾽[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 1217; ἀπονενιμμένος [prev. author] “Ec.” 419\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also in late Prose, see above; τῆς κρήνης -νιψάμενος[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.AD: Alciphro Epistolographus 3.1; but ἀπονίψασθαι τὸ πρόσωπον ἀπὸ τᾶς κράνας “IG” 4.951.63 (Epid.). \">Refs 4th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> rarely of things, ἀ. τὴν κύλικα[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pherecrates Comicus 41.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G0633","accentedUnicode":"ἀπονίπτω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0575","matchingForm":"ἀπό","stepTransliteration":"apo","gloss":"away from","_zh_tw_Gloss":"從","_es_Gloss":"de","_zh_Gloss":"从"},{"strongNumber":"G3538","matchingForm":"νίπτω","stepTransliteration":"niptō","gloss":"to wash","_zh_tw_Gloss":"洗","_es_Gloss":"lavar","_zh_Gloss":"洗"}],"shortDef":"to wash off","mediumDef":"to wash off <br /><b>to cleanse</b>, a part of the body <b>by washing;</b> <i>middle</i>, of one's self, <ref='Mat.27.24'>Mt. 27:24</ref>*","stepGloss":"to wash off","stepTransliteration":"aponiptō","count":1,"_es_Definition":"lavar ; med. lavarse","_zh_tw_Definition":"洗淨(自己) (太 27:24)","_zh_Definition":"洗净(自己) (太 27:24)","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"rửa sạch; rửa, làm sạch","_zh_tw_Gloss":"洗","_es_Gloss":"lavar","_zh_Gloss":"洗"}]}